quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,57,"Or he may say: \"If God had only guided me, I´d have been more heedful"
  39,58,"Or he may say as he sees the torment: \"If I only had another chance, then I´d be someone who acts kindly"
  39,59,"Of course My signs came to you, yet you rejected them and acted proudly, and were a disbeliever"
  39,60,On Resurrection Day you will see how the faces of the ones who have lied about God will be blackened. Is there not room in Hell for the overbearing
  39,61,"God will deliver the ones who have done their duty, to their place of achievement; evil will not touch them nor will they be saddened"
  39,62,God is the Creator of everything; He is in Charge of everything
  39,63,He holds the controls for Heaven and Earth while those who disbelieve in God´s signs will be the losers
  39,64,"SAY: \"Are you ordering me to worship somebody besides God, you know-nothings"
  39,65,"Yet there has been inspired in you as well as in those before you: ´If you associate [anything with God], your action will collapse and you will be a loser.´"
  39,66,"Rather you should worship God [Alone] and act grateful"
  39,67,"They have not valued God the way He should be valued. The whole earth will lie within His grasp on Resurrection Day, while Heaven will be folded up in His right hand. Glory be to Him; Exalted is He over anything they may associate [with Him]"